<subSubSection pageId="146" pageNumber="147" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="146.[136,778,1846,2093]" lastBlockId="146.[810,1452,158,474]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,258,1846,1872]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[361,476,1847,1873]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis box="[361,476,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="146" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 6 D–F) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName box="[568,713,1883,1910]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[568,713,1883,1910]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="142.[136,235,1421,1445]" captionTargetBox="[176,1391,200,1372]" captionTargetId="figure-233@142.[151,1435,189,1397]" captionTargetPageId="142" captionText="FIGURE 129. Actinopus laventana sp. nov., male: A–C LZI M135: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D FCE-MY 977: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597508/files/figure.png" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Fig. 129</figureCitation>
A–C) by the large, distally wide embolus and those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[170,292,1956,1983]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puelche">
<emphasis box="[170,292,1956,1983]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. puelche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[311,686,1956,1983]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 31 D–F) by the BTA medially placed. They differ from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[167,309,2030,2056]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[167,309,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the BTA displaced ventrally and from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[234,353,2066,2093]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puelche">
<emphasis box="[234,353,2066,2093]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. puelche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by more developed PA. Additionally, they resemble 
<taxonomicName box="[977,1120,158,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[977,1120,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1136,1283,159,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonia">
<emphasis box="[1136,1283,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. patagonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="146" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 29 E–G), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1248,1369,194,221]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puelche">
<emphasis box="[1248,1369,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. puelche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the embolus with three keels in prolateral view and a developed serrated area. They resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. patagonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[981,1101,303,330]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puelche">
<emphasis box="[981,1101,303,330]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. puelche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by PA continuous to PAc, and differ from 
<taxonomicName box="[940,1081,339,366]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[940,1081,339,366]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by PA continuous to PI.
</paragraph>
